Description: Flaring foot and floor sherd of East Greek pottery cup; floor, outside and stand-ring glazed; underside reserved; inscription cut on stand-ring.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of the Dioskouroi (Naukratis), Buried in sand under the west wall of Temenos.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXV, no. 677)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.201)
